fields.title: Extremely Busy
fields.body: So between legal registration, marketing, and programming, time is getting a little cramped with Yourbit. Yourbit is now approved to use the stripe connect API for accepting and distributing payments. I will be pushing to get the donation system implemented. Yourbit will be fundraising internally. Once thats done, Yourbit can be shared. We need donations to move forward with a few expensive tasks.

Bits are also gonna need overhauled again. Timezone conversion happens on feed load, the bits need to be loaded up in a different way. With this new method they will be prefetched in the backend. Which will actually make things a little bit faster. During prefetch, the date retrieved will be converted using pytz into the current timezone of the user. This will replace the actual UTC time in the database when sent to front end.

ANOTHER THING. So the way the space buttons had to work i had to declare iframe as a global variable. So some places in code broke, because yeah, they were also named iframe, so i have to change names. This is what they warn you about when they say “becareful with global variables” this is why the create bit panel doesn't hide on submission and feed doesn't reload and toggling colors off does not apply immediately
